1 state or a governmental subdivision authorized to issue permits.
2 (2) A license under this article is not required to perform
3 any of the following work:
4 (a) Minor repair work.
5 (b) The installation of a building sewer or water service
6 pipe, if a permit is secured from the responsible enforcing agency
7 and inspections are performed. The installations shall must comply
8 with the applicable parts of the state construction code.
9 (c) The installation of domestic water treatment and filtering
10 equipment that requires modification to an existing cold water
11 distribution supply and associated waste piping in buildings if a
12 permit is secured, required inspections performed, and the
13 installation complies with the applicable parts of the state
14 construction code. If the enforcing agency determines a violation
15 exists, the responsible installer must correct it.the violation.
16 (d) The installation by a homeowner of his or her the
17 homeowner's own plumbing, building sewer, or private sewer in his
18 or her the homeowner's single-family dwelling if a permit is
19 secured.
20 (e) The installation of medical gas piping, if the
21 installation is performed under the supervision of a licensed
22 plumbing contractor.
23 (f) The testing of a backflow preventer if the individual who
24 performs the testing holds an active ASSE 5110 certification as a
25 backflow prevention assembly tester.
26 (g) The testing of a backflow prevention assembly on an
27 automatic fire suppression system.
28 (3) This article does not prevent a person from performing any
29 activities within the scope of licensure or registration under any
